"""
=============================================================
  Thermal Camera — XIAO RP2040 + MLX90640 (110° FOV)
  Rainbow Heatmap  |  Dual Output  |  ~30 FPS
=============================================================

Hardware connections
--------------------
Raw MLX90640 chip (I2C1)  →  XIAO RP2040
  Pin 1 (VDD)  →  3V3
  Pin 2 (VSS)  →  GND
  Pin 3 (SDA)  →  GP6   (I2C1 SDA)
  Pin 4 (SCL)  →  GP7   (I2C1 SCL)

  REQUIRED external components (not on bare chip):
    4.7 kΩ resistor between GP6 (SDA) and 3V3  ← I2C pull-up
    4.7 kΩ resistor between GP7 (SCL) and 3V3  ← I2C pull-up
    100 nF ceramic capacitor between VDD and GND (place right at chip pins)

Buzzer    →  GP27  + GND  (active-high by default)
Power btn →  GP28  + GND  (internal pull-up)
Mode btn  →  GP29  + GND  (internal pull-up)

4-pin PCB output connector (I2C0 — second I2C bus)
----------------------------------------------------
  Pin 1  →  3V3          (power for external display)
  Pin 2  →  GND          (common ground)
  Pin 3  →  GP4  (SDA0)  (I2C data  → external display SDA)
  Pin 4  →  GP5  (SCL0)  (I2C clock → external display SCL)

  The RP2040 acts as I2C0 MASTER on this bus.
  The external display (e.g. SSD1306 OLED, SH1107, ST7789 via I2C)
  is the SLAVE. Frames are written to the display controller directly.

  Supported external display types (set EXT_DISPLAY_TYPE below):
    "SSD1306"  — 128×64 monochrome OLED  (I2C addr 0x3C or 0x3D)
    "SH1107"   — 128×128 monochrome OLED (I2C addr 0x3C)
    "NONE"     — 4-pin connector active but no rendering (raw I2C)

Output modes
------------
  MODE_USB  (0) : frames streamed over USB-CDC (Type-C → PC host_display.py)
  MODE_I2C  (1) : frames rendered on external I2C display (4-pin connector)
  MODE_BOTH (2) : USB-CDC stream AND I2C display simultaneously

Mode switching
--------------
  Short-press MODE_BTN  → cycle  USB → I2C → BOTH → USB …
  Long-press  MODE_BTN  → save current mode to flash (survives reboot)
  Short-press POWER_BTN → toggle streaming on/off
  Long-press  POWER_BTN → enter light-sleep (low power)

Startup mode priority
---------------------
  1. Saved mode in flash (output_mode.json) — if previously saved
  2. I2C display mode if an I2C display is detected on the 4-pin bus
  3. USB-CDC mode if a PC host is connected
  4. I2C mode as fallback (standalone use)

Buzzer feedback
---------------
  Power-on           : 1 long beep (200 ms)
  USB mode           : 1 medium beep
  I2C display mode   : 2 short beeps
  BOTH mode          : 3 short beeps
  Mode saved         : 3 short beeps
  Long-press sleep   : double beep
  No sensor error    : 5 rapid beeps

Protocol (USB-CDC binary, little-endian)
-----------------------------------------
  Offset  Size  Type      Field
  ------  ----  --------  --------------------------------
  0       4     uint32    Magic : 0xDEADBEEF
  4       2     uint16    Width  = 32
  6       2     uint16    Height = 24
  8       4     uint32    Frame index
  12      1     uint8     Output mode (0=USB 1=I2C 2=BOTH)
  13      3     uint8[3]  Reserved = 0x000000
  16      4     int32     T_min milli-°C
  20      4     int32     T_max milli-°C
  24      1536  uint16[]  Pixels: value = (T_°C + 40) × 100
  1560    2     uint16    Checksum (sum of pixel bytes & 0xFFFF)

Total = 1562 bytes per frame
=============================================================
"""

